    "body": "**Follow-up on dropped review comment:** the inline observation about the redundant outer Proxy in `generateFlatFactoryCode` was dropped by the inline diff-coverage check. Reposting here as a manual note:\n\nIn `packages/nextjs/src/config.ts`, `generateFlatFactoryCode` (lines 506ŌĆō522) wraps the result of `coreCreateEnv` in an outer Proxy whose server-only key access check duplicates the inner Proxy already returned by `createEnvInternal` (`create-env.ts:292ŌĆō295`). The outer Proxy uses the old error message format (`\"Accessing server-side environment variable...\"`) while the inner Proxy uses the updated `\"ArkEnv Error: Attempted to access...\"` format.\n\n`generateFactoryCode` and `generateClientFactoryCode` do NOT add their own outer Proxy ŌĆö only `generateFlatFactoryCode` does. Removing it would simplify the generated code, eliminate the error-message inconsistency, and reduce double-proxy overhead for every property access.\n\n<!-- PULLFROG_DIVIDER_DO_NOT_REMOVE_PLZ -->\n<sup><a href=\"https://pullfrog.com\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://pullfrog.com/logos/frog-white-full-18px.png\"><img src=\"https://pullfrog.com/logos/frog-green-full-18px.png\" width=\"9px\" height=\"9px\" style=\"vertical-align: middle; \" alt=\"Pullfrog\"></picture></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;’Į£ [View workflow run](https://github.com/yamcodes/arkenv/actions/runs/27837092273/job/82387543166) ’Į£ via [Pullfrog](https://pullfrog.com) ’Į£ Using `DeepSeek Pro` (free via [Pullfrog for OSS](https://pullfrog.com/for-oss)) ’Į£ [­ØĢÅ](https://x.com/pullfrogai)</sup>",
